      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "Live capture progress, leaner recall, async re-capture.\n\nWorks with any 0.2.x daemon (best with base 0.2.5, where re-capture runs in the background). Requires Obsidian ≥ 1.7.2. Khiip Plus lives on the daemon — the same plugin renders base or Plus output.\n\n## Added\n\n- **Live capture progress.** Capturing shows a staged progress card in the sidebar and a single updating notice (extract → … → embed) instead of a silent wait. Media downloads show per-item progress. The card sits pinned at the sidebar's bottom edge, clear of Obsidian's popup area.\n- **Async re-capture.** The ↻ re-capture path runs through the same staged card on a 0.2.5 daemon (\"Re-capturing … · stage\"), finishing with \"Refreshed: … — new version saved.\" On a 0.2.4 daemon it falls back to the classic synchronous refresh — same wording, with an immediate notice while it works.\n- **\"Khiip: re-capture this note\" command** — re-capture the note you're reading (reading mode; uses the note's khiip frontmatter).\n- **Leaner recall rows** with a 2-line excerpt showing *why* a result matched, plus relevance tiers on the score chip.\n- **@-handle chips** on X captures; web captures with no byline show the site hostname in the chip.\n- **Results header with ✕** (and Esc) to clear recall results back to the home view.\n\n## Fixed\n\n- The Khiip mark now renders correctly in the view tab, the sidebar header, and the capture modal (a CSS scoping bug displaced it from its slot — it also made the tab icon sit outside its own hover highlight).\n- Re-capturing against a 0.2.4 daemon shows feedback immediately instead of a silent wait, and a re-capture never stacks two popups for one action.\n- Internal cleanup from the pre-release review: dead client/type code removed; re-capture copy no longer depends on which daemon version answered.\n\n**Full changelog**: https://github.com/KhiipAI/khiip-obsidian/compare/0.2.4...0.2.5\n",
